3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although not the main focus of the paper, the concept of compressive sensing has applications in social and information networks, making this sub-category a possibility. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the performance of the constructed sensing matrices in sparse recovery, which is a numerical analysis problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The application of the constructed sensing matrices in harmonic detection can be considered a multimedia problem, as it involves the analysis of audio signals.
